[2;36m                    [0m                 at [1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFParser.parse[0m[1m([0mRTFParser.jav[1;92ma:70[0m[1m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 at [1;35mcom.example.RTFParserFuzzer.parseOne[0m[1m([0mRTFParserFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:53[0m[1m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 at [1;35mcom.example.RTFParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mRTFParserFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:40[0m[1m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: aa5f725795b842b8                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A Jazzer fuzzing run on an RTF parsing component triggered a high-severity security [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         finding: unrestricted deserialization of externally supplied data may allow remote  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         code execution. The fuzzer input caused a Java exception                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh`[1m)[0m during an              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ObjectInputStream.readObject` call, indicating that attacker-controlled data could [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         lead to the instantiation of arbitrary classes on the classpath.                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Issue Type                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           The fuzzer flagged a potential Remote Code Execution [1m([0mRCE[1m)[0m vulnerability arising  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         from unsafe deserialization. The specific finding is reported as                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote Code Execution`.                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - What Happened                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           During fuzz testing of an RTF parser harness [1m([0m`com.example.RTFParserFuzzer`[1m)[0m, an  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         input triggered Java deserialization via `ObjectInputStream.readObject`. This call  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         occurred in `jaz.Zer.readObject` and propagated up the call stack through Tika’s    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         RTF parser:                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m             • jaz.Zer.readObject [1m([0mline [1;36m377[0m[1m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m             • java.io.ObjectInputStream.readObject                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m             • org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mline [1;36m217[0m[1m)[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m             • org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.TextExtractor.processGroupEnd            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m             • org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.TextExtractor.extract                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m             • org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFParser.parseInline [35m/[0m parse            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m             • com.example.RTFParserFuzzer.parseOne [35m/[0m fuzzerTestOneInput                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Vulnerability Details                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           The vulnerability arises from “unrestricted class/object creation based on        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         externally controlled data,” a well-known deserialization weakness. If an attacker  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         can feed crafted RTF data containing serialized objects, the parser’s use of        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ObjectInputStream.readObject` can lead to instantiation of malicious classes       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         present on the classpath.                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Key Observations                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The failure occurs during handling of embedded OLE objects in RTF               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject`[1m)[0m.                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The Tika RTF parser uses Java’s built-in deserialization mechanism without      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         apparent checks on allowed classes.                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The fuzzer harness merely drives the parser and is not the root                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         cause—deserialization happens inside the parser code.                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The stack trace clearly shows the transition from the harness into              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ObjectInputStream` and back into parser logic, confirming the execution path that  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         leads to the finding.                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Code Areas to Investigate                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m1[0m. RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject [1m([0mRTFEmbObjHandler.jav[1;92ma:217[0m[1m)[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m2[0m. TextExtractor.processGroupEnd [35m/[0m extract [1m([0mTextExtractor.jav[1;92ma:1475[0m, [1;36m482[0m, [1;36m466[0m[1m)[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m3[0m. RTFParser.parseInline [35m/[0m parse [1m([0mRTFParser.jav[1;92ma:96[0m, [1;36m70[0m[1m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m4[0m. Any utility methods that wrap or invoke `ObjectInputStream.readObject` in this [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         codebase [1m([0me.g., jaz.Zer.readObject[1m)[0m.                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Investigating these locations will provide a holistic view of how external data     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         flows into the deserialization API and where class instantiation decisions are      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         made.                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m<[0m[1;95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== Java Exception: com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCode Execution[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUnrestricted class/object creation based on externally controlled data may allow[0m    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo eliminate the unrestricted‐deserialization RCE in [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m while preserving the parser’s [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39membedded‐object–processing logic, we will introduce a safe, class‐restricted [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mObjectInputStream and wire it in place of the existing raw call. The approach is:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Create a custom, whitelist‐based ObjectInputStream variant [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m“SafeRTFObjectInputStream”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the same package [0m[1;39m([0m[39morg.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add a new class:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     public class SafeRTFObjectInputStream extends ObjectInputStream [0m[1;39m{[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         private static final Set<String> ALLOWED_CLASSES = [0m[1;35mSet.of[0m[1;39m([0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"java.lang.String"[0m[39m,[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"java.lang.Integer"[0m[39m,[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"java.lang.Long"[0m[39m,[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"java.lang.Double"[0m[39m,[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"java.lang.Boolean"[0m[39m,[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"java.math.BigInteger"[0m[39m,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[32m"java.math.BigDecimal"[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         public [0m[1;35mSafeRTFObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream in[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35msuper[0m[1;39m([0m[39min[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         @Override[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         protected Class<?> [0m[1;35mresolveClass[0m[1;39m([0m[39mObjectStreamClass desc[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException [0m[1;39m{[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             String className = [0m[1;35mdesc.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mALLOWED_CLASSES.contains[0m[1;39m([0m[39mclassName[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 throw new [0m[1;35mInvalidClassException[0m[1;39m([0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     [0m[32m"Deserialization not allowed for class: "[0m[39m + className[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return [0m[1;35msuper.resolveClass[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdesc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This enforces that during [0m[1;35mreadObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, only the listed core [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJDK/primitive‐wrapper classes may be instantiated. Any other class triggers [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInvalidClassException.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Modify [0m[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to use SafeRTFObjectInputStream [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand correctly map its exceptions into Tika’s error-recording framework:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace the existing lines [0m[1;36m215[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m217[0m[39m:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         Object obj = new [0m[1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[1;35mUnsynchronizedByteArrayInputStream.builder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.setByteArray[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.g[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35met[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[1;35m.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - With:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSafeRTFObjectInputStream ois = new [0m[1;35mSafeRTFObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[1;35mUnsynchronizedByteArrayInputStream.builder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     [0m[1;35m.setByteArray[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             Object obj = [0m[1;35mois.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFMetadata.EMB_CLASS, [0m[1;35mobj.getClass[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 TikaCoreProperties.CONTENT_TYPE_PARSER_OVERRIDE,[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[1;35mMediaType.text[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"plain"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mextractObj[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mobj.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getBytes[0m[1;39m([0m[39mStandardCharsets.UTF_8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                        handler, metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInvalidClassException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Class not permitted by our whitelist; record and skip[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             throw new [0m[1;35mTikaException[0m[1;39m([0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[32m"Embedded Java object uses non‐whitelisted class: "[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 + [0m[1;35me.getMessage[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mClassNotFoundException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m original handling[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             throw new [0m[1;35mTikaException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Class not found in embedded Java object"[0m[39m, e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m I/O or stream errors[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             throw new [0m[1;35mTikaException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"I/O error during embedded‐object [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mdeserialization"[0m[39m, e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Because TextExtractor.processGroupEnd wraps [0m[1;35mhandleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m inside a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaException | IOException[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, any TikaException is recorded via [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mEmbeddedDocumentUtil.recordException[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and parsing continues without crashing the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser. Whitelisted classes [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. String, Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will still deserialize, enabling [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mtoString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` extraction.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional/Potential future enhancement[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Expose a ParseContext parameter and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser‐level toggle [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `RTFParser.ALLOW_JAVA_OBJECTS`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m so that advanced users [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan supply a custom whitelist or reenable unrestricted deserialization. Keep the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefault behavior locked down to our safe set.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preserve all existing parser‐wiring and harness logic:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes to RTFParser, TextExtractor, fuzz harness, or test code.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The new class lives alongside the handler; processGroupEnd and parser [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentrypoints remain untouched.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing tests continue to pass, except that malicious serialized classes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare now caught and recorded instead of permitting instantiation.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification & Side Effects:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By introducing a strict whitelist, we remove the avenue for arbitrary class [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstantiation, eliminating the RCE vector.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Legitimate embedded Java objects limited to simple types [0m[1;39m([0m[39mStrings, Numbers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinue to work, preserving core functionality.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any unrecognized or custom object types will be skipped with a recorded [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception, which is a documented fallback.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach reuses Java’s deserialization hooks [0m[1;39m([0m[39mresolveClass[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m rather than [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madding third‐party libs or breaking the harness.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Testing:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add unit tests deserializing a whitelisted String object—ensure extraction [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msucceeds.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add unit tests with a forbidden class [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., java.io.File[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m—ensure it throws [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTikaException and is recorded, not instantiated.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzz harness is unchanged; Jazzer runs should now see the unsafe branch caught[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand recorded rather than RCE.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCode ranges to update:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-microsoft-module/src/main/jav[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma/org/apache/tika/parser/microsoft/rtf/RTFEmbObjHandler.jav[0m[1;92ma:213[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m225[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-microsoft-module/src/main/jav[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [95mge[0m[39m>[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A Jazzer-based fuzz test reported a high-severity security finding—remote code      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         execution—when parsing embedded Java objects in RTF content. The vulnerable code in [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `RTFEmbObjHandler` uses a plain `ObjectInputStream` on attacker-controlled data. A  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         patch was attempted to replace it with `SafeRTFObjectInputStream`, add exception    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         handling for non-whitelisted classes [1m([0m`InvalidClassException`[1m)[0m, and improve error   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         reporting. After applying the patch, the Microsoft-RTF parser module failed to      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         compile with “cannot find symbol” errors for `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` and         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `InvalidClassException`.                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Initial issue                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Jazzer flagged `FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote Code Execution` because           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` deserializes arbitrary bytes via `new [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m[1;35m.readObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`.                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Stack trace highlights untrusted deserialization in:                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           - `org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject`   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           - calls to `[1;35mjava.io.ObjectInputStream.readObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - This allows an attacker to specify any class on the classpath and achieve RCE.    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch attempt                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - In the `EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA` branch of `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`, replaced:      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m             `Object obj = new [1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m[1;35m.readObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m;`                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           with:                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m             try-with-resources using `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` to read and safely filter   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         classes.                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Added metadata setting for embedded class name and forced plain-text content      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         type.                                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m44[0m[39m: * This class buffers data from embedded objects and pictures.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m45[0m[39m: * <p/>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m46[0m[39m: * <p/>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m47[0m[39m: * <p/>[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m48[0m[39m: * When the parser has finished an object or picture and called[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m49[0m[39m: * [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link #[0m[1;35mhandleCompletedObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m, this will write the object[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m50[0m[39m: * to the [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link #handler[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-micros[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moft-module/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/microsoft/rtf/RTFEmbObjHandler.jav[0m[1;92ma[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m:19[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m23[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m19[0m[39m:import java.io.IOException;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m20[0m[39m:import java.io.InputStream;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m21[0m[39m:import java.io.ObjectInputStream;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m22[0m[39m:import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m23[0m[39m:import java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Verify and add missing imports in RTFEmbObjHandler.java  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add at the top of `RTFEmbObjHandler.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39malongside the other `java.io` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimports[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     import java.io.InvalidClassException;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     import org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.SafeRTFObjectInputStream;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This resolves the “cannot find symbol” errors for both `InvalidClassException`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand `SafeRTFObjectInputStream`.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Create `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` in the Microsoft RTF parser module  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the same package [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add a new Java [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msource file:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     File:  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     tika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     tika-parser-microsoft-module/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/microsoft/rt[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mf/SafeRTFObjectInputStream.java[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Content:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     package org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     import java.io.InvalidClassException;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     import java.io.IOException;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     import java.io.InputStream;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     import java.io.ObjectInputStream;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     import java.io.ObjectStreamClass;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     import java.util.Collections;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     import java.util.HashSet;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     import java.util.Set;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * A subclass of ObjectInputStream that enforces a strict whitelist of allowed[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclasses[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * to prevent unsafe deserialization in RTF embedded objects.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     public class SafeRTFObjectInputStream extends ObjectInputStream [0m[1;39m{[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Define the allowed class names [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexpand as needed[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         private static final Set<String> ALLOWED_CLASSES;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         static [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             Set<String> s = new HashSet<>[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Core types[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35ms.add[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"java.lang.String"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35ms.add[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"java.lang.Integer"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35ms.add[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"java.lang.Long"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35ms.add[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"java.lang.Double"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35ms.add[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"java.lang.Float"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35ms.add[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"java.lang.Boolean"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35ms.add[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"java.math.BigDecimal"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Add other safe types if legitimate RTF objects require them[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             ALLOWED_CLASSES = [0m[1;35mCollections.unmodifiableSet[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         public [0m[1;35mSafeRTFObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mInputStream in[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35msuper[0m[1;39m([0m[39min[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         @Override[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         protected Class<?> [0m[1;35mresolveClass[0m[1;39m([0m[39mObjectStreamClass desc[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException [0m[1;39m{[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             String className = [0m[1;35mdesc.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mALLOWED_CLASSES.contains[0m[1;39m([0m[39mclassName[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 throw new [0m[1;35mInvalidClassException[0m[1;39m([0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         [0m[32m"Rejected deserialization of class: "[0m[39m + className, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclassName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return [0m[1;35msuper.resolveClass[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdesc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures that any attempt to deserialize an embedded Java object outside [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof the whitelist triggers `InvalidClassException`, which the handler already [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcatches and wraps in a `TikaException`.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Ensure the patched `RTFEmbObjHandler` uses the new class and exceptions [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrectly  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that the `JAVA_OBJDATA` branch now looks like:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstate == EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         try [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSafeRTFObjectInputStream ois =[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                     new [0m[1;35mSafeRTFObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                         [0m[1;35mUnsynchronizedByteArrayInputStream.builder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                             [0m[1;35m.setByteArray[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             Object obj = [0m[1;35mois.readObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFMetadata.EMB_CLASS, [0m[1;35mobj.getClass[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 TikaCoreProperties.CONTENT_TYPE_PARSER_OVERRIDE,[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[1;35mMediaType.text[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"plain"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mextractObj[0m[1;39m([0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[1;35mobj.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getBytes[0m[1;39m([0m[39mStandardCharsets.UTF_8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 handler, metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mInvalidClassException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             throw new [0m[1;35mTikaException[0m[1;39m([0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[32m"Embedded Java object uses non-whitelisted class: "[0m[39m + [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35me.getMessage[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mClassNotFoundException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             throw new [0m[1;35mTikaException[0m[1;39m([0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[32m"Class not found in embedded Java object"[0m[39m, e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             throw new [0m[1;35mTikaException[0m[1;39m([0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[32m"I/O error during embedded-object deserialization"[0m[39m, e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The imports at the top should now include both new lines for [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`InvalidClassException` and our `SafeRTFObjectInputStream`.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preserve existing functionality and security  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any previously supported embedded objects of whitelisted classes [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`String`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m still deserialize correctly.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The rest of `RTFEmbObjHandler` logic remains untouched; pictures and other [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstates operate as before.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch does not alter harness code, fuzzing logic, test code, or external [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdependencies, so existing tests and fuzzer entry points remain valid.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Validate and build  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re-run `mvn clean compile` in the microsoft-parser module; confirm no “cannot [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfind symbol” errors.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add a small unit test [0m[1;39m([0m[39moptional[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that attempts to deserialize a disallowed [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclass to verify `InvalidClassException` is thrown and correctly wrapped.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Implementing `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` directly in the RTF parser module ensures[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mno external library changes are required.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The whitelist approach directly addresses the root cause—unsafe [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialization—by preventing unknown classes from being loaded.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adding simple imports corrects the build errors without touching harnesses or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Similar patterns [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhitelisting in a custom `ObjectInputStream`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m exist elsewhere [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min Tika [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., in other parser modules[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, making this approach consistent with the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Potential side effects [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlegitimate but non-whitelisted embedded objects failing[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare acceptable given the security priority. If needed, extend the `ALLOWED_CLASSES`[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The initial issue is a high-severity Jazzer security finding flagged during         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         fuzzing: unrestricted Java object deserialization in RTFEmbObjHandler may allow     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         remote code execution. The proposed patch replaces `ObjectInputStream` with a new   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `SafeRTFObjectInputStream`, introduces class whitelisting, and improves exception   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         handling. After applying the patch, the build fails with “cannot find symbol:       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         SafeRTFObjectInputStream,” indicating the new class is neither present nor imported [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         correctly, causing compilation errors in the Microsoft RTF parser module.           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Initial Issue                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • A Jazzer fuzzer reported `FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote Code Execution` during  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         RTF parsing.                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • Stack trace shows `[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` calling `new      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m[1;35m.readObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`.                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • Unrestricted deserialization of external data can load arbitrary classes, leading [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         to RCE depending on the classpath.                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Important Observations                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • The insecure code path is in                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `tika-parser-microsoft-module/src/[33m...[0m[35m/[0m[95mRTFEmbObjHandler.java[0m` under the              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA` branch.                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • Deserialization is done via plain `ObjectInputStream`, with no class filtering or [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         sandbox.                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • The finding is reproducible via a libFuzzer input fed through                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `com.example.RTFParserFuzzer`.                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch Attempt                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • Imports added:                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           – `import org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.SafeRTFObjectInputStream;`         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           – `import java.io.InvalidClassException;`                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • In `EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA`, the code was rewritten to:                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m1[0m. Wrap the byte array in `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` instead of                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ObjectInputStream`.                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m2[0m. Read the object into `Object obj = [1;35mois.readObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`.                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m3[0m. Catch and rethrow `InvalidClassException`, `ClassNotFoundException`, and       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         general `IOException` as `TikaException` with descriptive messages.                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m4[0m. Use try-with-resources to ensure stream closure.                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Patch Result                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • Compilation errors in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`:                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           – “cannot find symbol: class SafeRTFObjectInputStream” [1m([0mthree occurrences[1m)[0m.       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • Indicates the `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` class is missing from the codebase or    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         not on the classpath.                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • The Microsoft parser module fails to compile, halting the build.                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Areas for Further Investigation                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • Verify that `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` is implemented and placed in               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf` [1m([0mor adjust package/imports[1m)[0m.                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • Check module dependencies to ensure the new class is included in the build.       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • Audit other deserialization usage sites in the RTF parser and across Tika to      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ensure consistent application of safe-stream wrappers.                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         • Review build configuration [1m([0mMaven module declarations[1m)[0m to confirm the parser      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         module can see the safe-input-stream class.                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
