[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Implement the missing SafeRTFObjectInputStream class in the Microsoft parser [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodule:[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Under src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/microsoft/rtf, create [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSafeRTFObjectInputStream.java.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Extend java.io.ObjectInputStream.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Override [0m[1;35mresolveClass[0m[1;39m([0m[39mObjectStreamClass[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m[1;35mresolveProxyClass[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecking each class name against a hard-coded whitelist of allowed types [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjava.lang.String, java.lang.Integer, java.util.Date[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. If a name is not on the list,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrow java.io.InvalidClassException.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Provide a public constructor that takes an InputStream and calls [0m[1;35msuper[0m[1;39m([0m[39min[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensuring stream header is read.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. Keep the class package-private or public as needed; it must match the import [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min RTFEmbObjHandler.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Adjust RTFEmbObjHandler imports and code:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Remove import of java.io.ObjectInputStream [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno longer used[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Add imports for:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        import java.io.InvalidClassException;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        import org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.SafeRTFObjectInputStream;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. In the EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA branch, use try-with-resources to instantiate [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSafeRTFObjectInputStream over the UnsynchronizedByteArrayInputStream builder, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mreadObject[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, then set metadata and call extractObj, exactly as in the last patch [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempt.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Catch InvalidClassException, ClassNotFoundException, and IOException [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseparately, wrapping each in a TikaException with a descriptive message.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Verify module boundaries and dependencies:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Since SafeRTFObjectInputStream lives in the same module, no changes to pom.xml[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare required.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure package declaration in SafeRTFObjectInputStream.java is [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf so that the import resolves.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preserve existing functionality and tests:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whitelist at least all classes historically deserialized by RTFEmbObjHandler [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., String for embedded text[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. If future tests or test harnesses require [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madditional classes, add them to the whitelist.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This change will reject any previously accepted non-whitelisted types, but [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat is the intentional security hardening.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All other EMB_STATE branches remain untouched, and fuzzing entry points are [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Optional audit:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Search the RTF parser codebase for any other direct uses of ObjectInputStream [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand apply a similar wrapper if needed.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add unit tests in the parser module to validate SafeRTFObjectInputStream [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdeserializing a whitelist class succeeds; a non-whitelisted class throws [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInvalidClassException[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The compilation failure [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“cannot find symbol: SafeRTFObjectInputStream”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolved by providing the class in the expected package.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By implementing the safe stream locally, we avoid adding cross-module [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdependencies or modifying external libraries.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Overriding resolveClass/respectively ensures only approved classes are [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialized, directly eliminating the RCE risk flagged by Jazzer.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The RTFEmbObjHandler logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmetadata setting, extractObj invocation[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is unchanged[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexcept for stream construction, so existing parsing behavior [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor allowed classes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis preserved.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Failure to deserialize disallowed classes surfaces as a clear TikaException, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreventing silent bypass of the security control.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The initial issue is a high-severity Jazzer finding indicating potential remote     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         code execution via unrestricted Java deserialization in the RTFEmbObjHandler. The   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         patch attempt replaces direct use of `ObjectInputStream` with a new                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` to enforce a class whitelist and catch invalid classes.  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         After applying the patch, the build fails in the Microsoft RTF parser module with   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         compilation errors because `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` cannot be found.              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A Jazzer fuzzer detected                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote Code Execution`.  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The stack trace shows RTFEmbObjHandler invoking `new [1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         on untrusted byte data.                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Unrestricted deserialization of external data can load arbitrary classes on    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the classpath, leading to RCE.                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Key Observations in the Initial Issue                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The vulnerable code lives in `RTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject`, state   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `EMB_STATE.JAVA_OBJDATA`.                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Deserialization uses `java.io.ObjectInputStream` without any class filtering.  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - No existing mechanism in that handler restricts which types can be             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         instantiated.                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Removed import of `java.io.ObjectInputStream`.                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Added imports:                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • `java.io.InvalidClassException`                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • `org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.SafeRTFObjectInputStream`              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Replaced raw `new [1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` with a try-with-resources opening a  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` on the same byte input stream.                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - On `InvalidClassException`, throws a `TikaException` indicating                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         non-whitelisted class use.                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Refined error handling for `ClassNotFoundException` and generalized            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `IOException`.                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Patch Result and Build Log                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Compilation errors in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java` at import and usage sites:       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Cannot find symbol `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` in package.                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Three errors: missing class symbol at the import line and two usages in      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         code.                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - All other modules compile successfully; failure occurs only in the Microsoft   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         RTF parser module.                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. Areas for Further Investigation                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Verify that `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` is defined and accessible in the        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf` package or add it to the module’s source.    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Review the RTF parser module’s package structure to ensure the new class is    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         included in the build.                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Inspect the implementation or availability of a class-whitelisting stream      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         wrapper elsewhere in Tika to determine if it needs importing or creation.           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Examine `UnsynchronizedByteArrayInputStream` and surrounding code in           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `RTFEmbObjHandler` to confirm compatibility with the safe input stream.             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Evaluate module dependencies and Maven settings to confirm that any new        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         classes are compiled and packaged for this module.                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ---                                                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Analysis [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Analysis Report[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mUnsynchronizedByteArrayInputStream.builder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.setByteArray[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m218[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRTFMetadata.EMB_CLASS, [0m[1;35mobj.getClass[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m219[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mmetadata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaCoreProperties.CONTENT_TYPE_PARSER_OVERRIDE,[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m220[0m[39m:                        [0m[1;35mMediaType.text[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"plain"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m221[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mextractObj[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mobj.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getBytes[0m[1;39m([0m[39mStandardCharsets.UTF_8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandler, metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview of the fix  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   To resolve the compilation errors and close the RCE hole, we need to introduce [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mour own safe deserialization wrapper in the Microsoft RTF parser module [0m[1;39m([0m[39msince [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`SafeRTFObjectInputStream` doesn’t exist elsewhere[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This wrapper will extend [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ObjectInputStream`, override class resolution to enforce an explicit whitelist, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand throw `InvalidClassException` for any non-approved types. We then wire it into [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RTFEmbObjHandler` in place of the raw `ObjectInputStream`.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Create `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` in the RTF parser module  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Under  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      tika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      tika-parser-microsoft-module/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/microsoft/r[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtf/  [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      add a new file `SafeRTFObjectInputStream.java`.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In that file:  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Declare `package org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf;`  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Extend `java.io.ObjectInputStream` and define a static whitelist of class [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnames [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. `java.lang.String`, boxed primitives, common value types[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Override the protected `[0m[1;35mresolveClass[0m[1;39m([0m[39mObjectStreamClass desc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method. If [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mdesc.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is not in the whitelist, throw `InvalidClassException`. Otherwise [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdelegate to `[0m[1;35msuper.resolveClass[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdesc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Provide a public constructor that accepts an `InputStream` and calls [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35msuper[0m[1;39m([0m[39min[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Update `RTFEmbObjHandler` to use the new wrapper  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Remove import of `java.io.ObjectInputStream`.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Add import for our new `SafeRTFObjectInputStream`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Replace the `new [0m[1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block with a try-with-resources on [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`SafeRTFObjectInputStream`.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Catch `InvalidClassException`, wrapping it in a `TikaException` with an [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplanatory message.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. Retain the existing catches for `ClassNotFoundException` and general [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`IOException`.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preserve existing functionality  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The handler still reads an embedded Java object, records its class name, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcoerces it to plain text, and hands off to `[0m[1;35mextractObj[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We only introduce additional rejection logic when a non-whitelisted class is [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mencountered.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other module or harness code is touched; tests that rely on embedded-object[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraction for whitelisted types continue to pass.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Module packaging  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Because `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` lives alongside `RTFEmbObjHandler` in the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame Maven module, no changes to `pom.xml` are necessary. The new source file will [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe compiled automatically.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Side-effects and mitigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Embedded objects of types outside the whitelist will now fail with a clear [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexception rather than risk remote code execution.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If certain legitimate types [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. `java.util.Date`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are needed in real inputs,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthey can be added to the static whitelist in `SafeRTFObjectInputStream`.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We avoid any broad exception-swallowing or harness modifications, maintaining [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompatibility with existing fuzzers and test suites.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Reference pattern  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar patterns exist in other parsers [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. safe wrappers in the Office or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mXML modules[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m where deserialization is restricted via an allow-list in a custom [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ObjectInputStream` subclass. We mirror that design within the RTF parser module.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis approach restores a clean build, enforces strong deserialization controls, and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mkeeps all existing functionality intact.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A Jazzer fuzzing run against the Apache Tika RTF parser uncovered a high-severity   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         security finding: untrusted deserialization in `RTFEmbObjHandler` that could enable [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         remote code execution. To address it, the patch replaces the raw                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ObjectInputStream` usage with a proposed `SafeRTFObjectInputStream`, adds          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         exception handling for non-whitelisted classes and I/O errors, and updates metadata [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         accordingly. However, the build fails: the class `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` cannot  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         be found, leading to compilation errors in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`.                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Jazzer reported `FuzzerSecurityIssueHigh: Remote Code Execution` in RTF object [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         embedding handling.                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The problematic code path is in `[1;35mRTFEmbObjHandler.handleCompletedObject[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`, [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         where it deserializes embedded Java objects via a plain `new                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m[1;35m.readObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`.                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Such unguarded deserialization on attacker-controlled data may allow           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         instantiation of arbitrary classes on the classpath, leading to code execution.     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Key Observations from the Fuzzing Log                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The stack trace pinpoints `RTFEmbObjHandler.jav[1;92ma:217[0m` [1m([0mthe call to             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mreadObject[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`[1m)[0m as the source.                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - No defenses [1m([0mlike a validation whitelist or a custom `ObjectInputStream`[1m)[0m are  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         in place in the current parser implementation.                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The finding is classified “high” because deserialization of untrusted data is  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         a well-known critical risk.                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - In `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`:                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Removed `import java.io.ObjectInputStream`.                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Added `import org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.SafeRTFObjectInputStream` [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         and `import java.io.InvalidClassException`.                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Replaced the plain `new [1;35mObjectInputStream[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` block with a                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         try-with-resources on `SafeRTFObjectInputStream`.                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • After reading the object, it sets metadata and processes the object safely   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         as plain text.                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Introduced new catch blocks for `InvalidClassException`,                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `ClassNotFoundException`, and generic `IOException`, each re-thrown as a            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `TikaException` with descriptive messages.                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Patch Result                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The Maven compile phase fails in the Microsoft parser module:                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Three “cannot find symbol” errors all point to `SafeRTFObjectInputStream`    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mimport and usage sites[1m)[0m.                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - This indicates the new class `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` is neither present in  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         this module nor resolvable from any other module on the classpath.                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. Areas for Further Investigation                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Locate or create the `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` implementation:                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Check whether a general-purpose safe deserialization utility already exists  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         elsewhere in Tika [1m([0me.g., in `tika-core` or other parser modules[1m)[0m.                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • If not present, author the class in `tika-parser-microsoft-module` under     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf`.                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Verify the intended whitelist mechanism for deserialization:                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Determine which classes should be allowed.                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Ensure the safe-stream enforces this whitelist and throws                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `InvalidClassException` appropriately.                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Confirm packaging and module dependencies:                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • If `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` lives in another module, add the necessary     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Maven dependency.                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Update module’s `pom.xml` if linking to a common deserialization-guard       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         library.                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Review build configuration for consistency:                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Ensure new source files are included in the build.                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Verify import paths and package declarations match the filesystem layout.    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-micros[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moft-module/pom.xml:[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m60[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m:<?xml [0m[33mversion[0m[39m=[0m[32m"1[0m[32m.0"[0m[39m [0m[33mencoding[0m[39m=[0m[32m"UTF[0m[32m-8"[0m[39m?>[0m                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m44[0m[39m:    <dependency>[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m45[0m[39m:      <groupId>$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mproject.groupId[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mgroupId[0m[39m>[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m46[0m[39m:      <artifactId>tika-parser-text-module<[0m[35m/[0m[95martifactId[0m[39m>[0m                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m51[0m[39m:      <artifactId>tika-parser-xml-module<[0m[35m/[0m[95martifactId[0m[39m>[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m52[0m[39m:      <version>$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mproject.version[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mversion[0m[39m>[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m53[0m[39m:    <[0m[35m/[0m[95mdependency[0m[39m>[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m54[0m[39m:    <!-- needed for msg files -->[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m55[0m[39m:    <dependency>[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m56[0m[39m:      <groupId>$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mproject.groupId[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mgroupId[0m[39m>[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m57[0m[39m:      <artifactId>tika-parser-mail-commons<[0m[35m/[0m[95martifactId[0m[39m>[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m:      <version>$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mproject.version[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mversion[0m[39m>[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m59[0m[39m:    <[0m[35m/[0m[95mdependency[0m[39m>[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m:    <dependency>[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Create `SafeRTFObjectInputStream` in the Microsoft-RTF parser module**  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Under [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-micro[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msoft-module/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/microsoft/rtf/`, add a new file [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`SafeRTFObjectInputStream.java` with package declaration [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf`.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Implement it as a subclass of `java.io.ObjectInputStream`. In its constructor,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccept an `InputStream` and call `[0m[1;35msuper[0m[1;39m([0m[39min[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Define a static, immutable whitelist of class names that are safe to [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeserialize [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor instance, `java.lang.String`, primitive wrappers, and any other [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclasses Tika can safely convert via `[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Override `protected Class<?> [0m[1;35mresolveClass[0m[1;39m([0m[39mObjectStreamClass desc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and throw [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`InvalidClassException` if `[0m[1;35mdesc.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is not in the whitelist; otherwise, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdelegate to `[0m[1;35msuper.resolveClass[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdesc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similarly override `protected Class<?> [0m[1;35mresolveProxyClass[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m interfaces[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mif needed[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to prevent proxy‐based attacks by rejecting non‐whitelisted interface [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msets.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Re-apply the patch in `RTFEmbObjHandler.java`**  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep the `try-with-resources` block wrapping the raw bytes in [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`SafeRTFObjectInputStream`.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Retain the existing `catch` blocks for `InvalidClassException`, [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ClassNotFoundException`, and `IOException`, each re-throwing as `TikaException` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith clear messages.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure you remove the old `import java.io.ObjectInputStream` and add:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     import java.io.InvalidClassException;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     import org.apache.tika.parser.microsoft.rtf.SafeRTFObjectInputStream;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **No changes to `pom.xml`, harness, or external dependencies**  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Since Maven compiles all `.java` under `src/main/java` by default, adding [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`SafeRTFObjectInputStream.java` suffices.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Do not modify any fuzzing or test code; they will now see safe deserialization[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menforced.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Why this is optimal**  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Security**: Blocks unsafe classes at deserialization time, mitigating RCE risk [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon untrusted RTF embeddings.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Compatibility**: Preserves existing flow—reads an object, extracts its class [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mname, converts to text—only restricting classes that could introduce code.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Minimal impact**: No changes to build scripts or external modules. Existing [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munit tests and fuzz harness remain unchanged and will now catch malicious payloads [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvia the new class.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side-effect considerations**  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Legitimate embeddings of custom objects**: Will now throw `TikaException`. If [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbroad compatibility is needed, the whitelist can be extended.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Performance**: Whitelist check adds a tiny constant overhead per `resolveClass`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall; acceptable given security gains.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Future maintenance**: Keep the whitelist centralized in [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`SafeRTFObjectInputStream`. Any new safe types can be added there.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
